data.name: Herb-Crusted Rack of Lamb with Roasted Root Vegetables
data.quickTastyDescription: A succulent rack of lamb coated in a fragrant herb crust, served with a medley of caramelized root vegetables.
detailedCookingInstructions: In a bowl, mix rosemary, thyme, minced garlic, olive oil, salt, and pepper to create a herb paste.
Rub the herb paste all over the rack of lamb, ensuring even coverage.
In a roasting pan, toss the diced carrots, parsnips, and sweet potatoes with olive oil, salt, and pepper. Spread them in an even layer.
Place the rack of lamb on top of the vegetables and roast in the preheated oven for about 25-30 minutes for medium-rare, or until desired doneness.
Remove from oven and let the lamb rest for 10 minutes before slicing into chops.
Serve the lamb chops alongside the roasted root vegetables.
